## 1. Kansas City Fed PCA (KC-RORO)

**Total Inputs:** 18 financial series  
**Frequency:** Daily (close-to-close)  
**Transformation:** First differences (log for levels, arithmetic for spreads), then z-score normalization over rolling 520-day window

### 1.1 Credit Risk Factors (3 inputs)

| # | Series Name | Ticker/Source | Type | Transformation | Sign Convention |
|---|-------------|---------------|------|----------------|-----------------|
| 1 | US BBB Corporate OAS | BAMLC0A4CBBB (FRED) | Spread (bps) | $\Delta \text{OAS}_t$ | +1 (wider = risk-off) |
| 2 | Euro BBB Corporate OAS | BAMLHE00EBBBEY (FRED) | Spread (bps) | $\Delta \text{OAS}_t$ | +1 |
| 3 | BAA-10Y Treasury Spread | BAA10Y (FRED) | Spread (bps) | $\Delta S_t$ | +1 |

**Detail:**
- OAS = Option-Adjusted Spread (removes embedded optionality)
- BBB = Investment-grade corporate bonds (Baa2/BBB rated)
- BAA-10Y = Moody's BAA yield minus 10-year Treasury constant maturity

### 1.2 Equity Market Factors (5 inputs)

| # | Series Name | Ticker/Source | Type | Transformation | Sign Convention |
|---|-------------|---------------|------|----------------|-----------------|
| 4 | S&P 500 Total Return | SP500TR (Bloomberg) | Price index | $-\Delta \log(P_t)$ | -1 (decline = risk-off) |
| 5 | STOXX 600 Total Return | SXXR (Bloomberg) | Price index | $-\Delta \log(P_t)$ | -1 |
| 6 | MSCI Advanced Economies | MXEA (Bloomberg) | Price index | $-\Delta \log(P_t)$ | -1 |
| 7 | **VIX (Equity Implied Vol)** | VIX (CBOE) | Implied volatility (%) | $\Delta \text{VIX}_t$ | +1 (higher vol = risk-off) |
| 8 | **VSTOXX (Euro Equity Implied Vol)** | V2X (Eurex) | Implied volatility (%) | $\Delta \text{VSTOXX}_t$ | +1 |

**Detail:**
- Total return indices include dividends
- Log returns ensure stationarity and comparability across levels
- VIX = CBOE Volatility Index (30-day implied vol from S&P 500 options)
- VSTOXX = EURO STOXX 50 Volatility Index (30-day implied vol)

### 1.3 Funding Liquidity Factors (6 inputs)

| # | Series Name | Ticker/Source | Type | Transformation | Sign Convention |
|---|-------------|---------------|------|----------------|-----------------|
| 9 | 2-Year Treasury G-Spread | FRED/Bloomberg | Spread (bps) | $\Delta G_{2Y,t}$ | +1 (wider = risk-off) |
| 10 | 5-Year Treasury G-Spread | FRED/Bloomberg | Spread (bps) | $\Delta G_{5Y,t}$ | +1 |
| 11 | 10-Year Treasury G-Spread | FRED/Bloomberg | Spread (bps) | $\Delta G_{10Y,t}$ | +1 |
| 12 | TED Spread | TEDRATE (FRED) | Spread (bps) | $\Delta \text{TED}_t$ | +1 |
| 13 | LIBOR-OIS Spread | Bloomberg | Spread (bps) | $\Delta (\text{LIBOR} - \text{OIS})_t$ | +1 |
| 14 | 3-Month Treasury Bid-Ask | Bloomberg BVAL | Liquidity measure (bps) | $\Delta \text{BidAsk}_t$ | +1 (wider = illiquid) |

**Detail:**
- **G-Spread** = Treasury yield - OIS (Overnight Index Swap) rate
  - Measures credit/liquidity premium in Treasury market
- **TED Spread** = 3-month LIBOR - 3-month Treasury bill rate
  - Classic bank credit risk indicator
- **LIBOR-OIS** = 3-month LIBOR - 3-month OIS
  - Interbank credit/liquidity premium
- **Bid-Ask Spread** = (Ask - Bid) / Mid
  - Direct measure of market liquidity

### 1.4 Currency & Commodity Factors (2 inputs)

| # | Series Name | Ticker/Source | Type | Transformation | Sign Convention |
|---|-------------|---------------|------|----------------|-----------------|
| 15 | US Dollar Index | DXY (ICE) | FX index | $\Delta \log(\text{DXY}_t)$ | +1 (stronger USD = risk-off) |
| 16 | Gold Spot Price | XAUUSD (Bloomberg) | Commodity (USD/oz) | $\Delta \log(P_{\text{Gold},t})$ | +1 (gold rally = risk-off) |

**Detail:**
- DXY = Trade-weighted USD index vs. basket of 6 major currencies (EUR, JPY, GBP, CAD, SEK, CHF)
- Gold = Safe-haven asset, inverse correlation with risk appetite

### 1.5 Missing: Implied Vol Term Structure Inputs

**PROPOSED ADDITIONS (not in original KC spec but critical):**

| # | Series Name | Construction | Type | Transformation |
|---|-------------|--------------|------|----------------|
| 17 | **VIX Term Structure Slope** | $\text{VIX}_{3M} - \text{VIX}_{1M}$ | Vol slope (pp) | $\Delta \text{Slope}_t$ |
| 18 | **MOVE Index (Bond Vol)** | Merrill Lynch Option Volatility Estimate | Implied vol (bps) | $\Delta \text{MOVE}_t$ |
| 19 | **CVIX (Currency Vol)** | JPM G7 Currency Volatility Index | Implied vol (%) | $\Delta \text{CVIX}_t$ |
| 20 | **SKEW Index** | CBOE S&P 500 Tail Risk | Skewness measure | $\Delta \text{SKEW}_t$ |

**Rationale:**
- **Vol slope** captures risk premium term structure (contango vs. backwardation)
- **MOVE** captures bond market uncertainty (complements equity vol)
- **CVIX** captures FX market stress
- **SKEW** captures tail risk perception (crash probability)

