## 3. Baker-Wurgler Sentiment PCA

**Total Inputs:** 6 behavioral proxies (monthly frequency)  
**Frequency:** Monthly (end-of-month aggregates)  
**Transformation:** Orthogonalize w.r.t. 6 macro factors, then PCA on residuals

### 3.1 Primary Sentiment Proxies (6 inputs)

| # | Proxy Name | Source | Measurement | Economic Interpretation |
|---|------------|--------|-------------|-------------------------|
| 1 | **Closed-End Fund Discount (CEFD)** | CRSP/Morningstar | $\text{CEFD}_t = \frac{1}{N}\sum_{j} \frac{\text{NAV}_{j,t} - P_{j,t}}{\text{NAV}_{j,t}}$ | Irrational pessimism when discount widens |
| 2 | **NYSE Share Turnover (TURN)** | NYSE/CRSP | $\text{TURN}_t = \frac{\text{Volume}_t}{\text{Shares Listed}_t}$ | High turnover = speculative frenzy |
| 3 | **Number of IPOs (NIPO)** | Jay Ritter IPO Database | Count of IPOs in month $t$ | Firms time issues to exploit optimism |
| 4 | **First-Day IPO Returns (RIPO)** | Jay Ritter IPO Database | $\text{RIPO}_t = \frac{1}{N}\sum_{j} \frac{P_{\text{close},j} - P_{\text{offer},j}}{P_{\text{offer},j}}$ | High returns = investor exuberance |
| 5 | **Equity Share in New Issues (ES)** | SDC Platinum | $\text{ES}_t = \frac{\text{Equity Issues}_t}{\text{Equity} + \text{Debt Issues}_t}$ | High equity share = low perceived cost of equity |
| 6 | **Dividend Premium (DP)** | CRSP | $\text{DP}_t = \log\left(\frac{\bar{M/B}_{\text{payers}}}{\bar{M/B}_{\text{non-payers}}}\right)$ | Low/negative premium = preference for speculative stocks |

### 3.2 Macro Control Variables (6 inputs for orthogonalization)

| # | Variable | Source | Transformation | Purpose |
|---|----------|--------|----------------|---------|
| 1 | **Industrial Production Growth** | FRED (INDPRO) | $\Delta \log(\text{IP}_t)$ | Remove business cycle |
| 2 | **Consumer Sentiment** | Univ. Michigan (UMCSENT) | Level | Remove confidence cycle |
| 3 | **Term Spread** | FRED | $y_{10Y,t} - y_{3M,t}$ | Remove monetary policy stance |
| 4 | **Default Spread** | FRED | $y_{\text{BAA},t} - y_{\text{AAA},t}$ | Remove credit conditions |
| 5 | **Lagged S&P 500 Return** | CRSP | $R_{\text{SPX}, t-1}$ | Remove momentum |
| 6 | **NBER Recession Indicator** | FRED (USREC) | Binary {0,1} | Remove recession effects |

**Orthogonalization Process:**

For each proxy $k$:
$$X_{k,t} = \beta_{k,0} + \sum_{j=1}^{6} \beta_{k,j} \text{Macro}_{j,t} + \varepsilon_{k,t}$$

Use residual $\varepsilon_{k,t}$ as "pure sentiment" component.

### 3.3 Missing: Market Microstructure Variables

**PROPOSED ADDITIONS:**

| # | Variable | Construction | Rationale |
|---|----------|--------------|-----------|
| 7 | **Retail Flow Intensity** | Retail buy volume / Total volume | Direct sentiment measure |
| 8 | **Short Interest Ratio** | Avg short interest / Avg daily volume | Sophisticated investor pessimism |
| 9 | **Options Volume Ratio** | Put volume / Call volume | Hedging vs. speculation |
| 10 | **Margin Debt Growth** | $\Delta \log(\text{NYSE Margin Debt})$ | Leverage = overconfidence |

