## 4. Baker-Wurgler PLS Enhanced

**Total Inputs:** Same 6 proxies as BW-PCA + target variable  
**Frequency:** Monthly → interpolated to daily via EWMA  
**Key Difference:** Supervised learning (uses credit spread changes as target)

### 4.1 Predictor Variables (6 inputs - identical to Section 3.1)

Same as Baker-Wurgler PCA (CEFD, TURN, NIPO, RIPO, ES, DP)

### 4.2 Target Variables (for PLS optimization)

| Horizon | Target | Definition | Use Case |
|---------|--------|------------|----------|
| $h=1$ day | $Y_{t+1}$ | $\Delta S_{t+1} = S_{t+1} - S_t$ | Tactical trading |
| $h=5$ days | $Y_{t+5}$ | $\Delta S_{t+5} = S_{t+5} - S_t$ | Weekly positioning |
| $h=20$ days | $Y_{t+20}$ | $\Delta S_{t+20} = S_{t+20} - S_t$ | Monthly allocation |

Where $S_t$ is credit spread (CDX IG, CDX HY, or iTraxx Europe)

### 4.3 PLS Algorithm Mechanics

**Difference from PCA:**
- PCA: Maximize $\text{Var}(\mathbf{w}^\top \mathbf{X})$
- PLS: Maximize $\text{Cov}^2(\mathbf{w}^\top \mathbf{X}, Y_{t+h})$

**Output:** Direction $\mathbf{w}^{PLS}$ that best predicts future spread changes

### 4.4 Monthly-to-Daily Interpolation (EWMA)

**Input:** Monthly sentiment $\{\text{SENT}_m\}_{m=1,2,\ldots}$

**Output:** Daily sentiment $\{\text{SENT}_{t,d}\}_{t=1,2,\ldots,T}$

**Algorithm:**
$$\text{SENT}_{t,d} = \begin{cases}
\text{SENT}_m & \text{if } t \text{ is month-end} \\
\rho \cdot \text{SENT}_{t-1,d} + (1-\rho) \cdot \text{SENT}_m & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}$$

where $\rho = \exp(-1/21) \approx 0.953$ (21 trading days/month).

