## 7. AUD/JPY FX Index

**Total Inputs:** 1 currency pair (tick-level)  
**Frequency:** Tick (bid/ask quotes) aggregated to 1-min or 5-min bars  
**Transformation:** Log price, optionally velocity-adjusted

### 7.1 Primary Input (1)

| # | Series | Pair | Type | Frequency | Source |
|---|--------|------|------|-----------|--------|
| 1 | **AUD/JPY Spot** | Australian Dollar / Japanese Yen | FX spot rate | Tick (bid/ask) | Reuters/EBS/Bloomberg |

**Rationale:**
- AUD = commodity currency (risk-on)
- JPY = safe-haven currency (risk-off)
- Pair captures risk appetite directly

### 7.2 Derived Indices

**Level-Based:**
$$\text{RORO}_t^{\text{FX}} = \log(S_t^{\text{AUD/JPY}})$$

**Velocity-Adjusted:**
$$\text{RORO}_t^{\text{FX,vel}} = \frac{1}{\sigma_{\text{vol}}} \cdot \frac{d}{dt}\log(S_t^{\text{AUD/JPY}})$$

where $\sigma_{\text{vol}}$ = rolling 20-day realized volatility:

$$\sigma_{\text{vol},t} = \sqrt{\frac{252}{20}\sum_{s=t-19}^{t} \left(\Delta \log(S_s)\right)^2}$$

### 7.3 Alternative Pairs (for robustness)

| # | Pair | Rationale |
|---|------|-----------|
| 2 | **NZD/JPY** | Similar risk-on/safe-haven dynamic |
| 3 | **AUD/CHF** | Commodity vs. European safe haven |
| 4 | **EUR/JPY** | European growth vs. yen safety |

### 7.4 Missing: FX Vol Surface Inputs

**PROPOSED ADDITIONS:**

| # | Variable | Construction | Rationale |
|---|----------|--------------|-----------|
| 5 | **AUD/JPY 1M Implied Vol** | ATM vol from options | FX market stress |
| 6 | **AUD/JPY Risk Reversal** | 25Δ call IV - 25Δ put IV | Directional skew |
