## 8. Moving Average Count (MAC) Index

**Total Inputs:** 10 ETF price series (5 risk + 5 safe)  
**Frequency:** Daily or hourly  
**Transformation:** Binary MA(200) indicator per asset, then basket differential

### 8.1 Risk Asset Basket (5 inputs)

| # | Ticker | Asset Class | Benchmark | Rationale |
|---|--------|-------------|-----------|-----------|
| 1 | **SPY** | US Large-Cap Equity | S&P 500 | Core equity risk |
| 2 | **QQQ** | US Tech Equity | NASDAQ-100 | Growth/tech exposure |
| 3 | **HYG** | High-Yield Bonds | iShares HY Corp | Credit risk |
| 4 | **EEM** | Emerging Market Equity | MSCI EM | EM equity risk |
| 5 | **JNK** | High-Yield Bonds (alt) | SPDR Bloomberg HY | Credit risk (alt) |

### 8.2 Safe Asset Basket (5 inputs)

| # | Ticker | Asset Class | Benchmark | Rationale |
|---|--------|-------------|-----------|-----------|
| 6 | **TLT** | Long-Duration Treasuries | 20+ Year UST | Duration/safety |
| 7 | **GLD** | Gold | Physical gold | Safe haven commodity |
| 8 | **UUP** | US Dollar | USD Index | Safe haven FX |
| 9 | **IEF** | Intermediate Treasuries | 7-10 Year UST | Core fixed income |
| 10 | **XLU** | Utilities Equity | Utilities Select Sector | Defensive equity |

### 8.3 Indicator Construction

**Per-Asset Binary Indicator:**
$$I_{a,t} = \mathbb{1}\{P_{a,t} > \text{MA}_{200}(P_{a,t})\}$$

**Index:**
$$\text{RORO}_t^{\text{MAC}} = \frac{1}{5}\sum_{a \in \text{Risk}} I_{a,t} - \frac{1}{5}\sum_{a \in \text{Safe}} I_{a,t}$$

**Range:** $[-1, +1]$
- +1 = All risk assets above MA(200), all safe assets below (extreme risk-on)
- -1 = All risk assets below MA(200), all safe assets above (extreme risk-off)

