## 10. Hybrid Sentiment-SVAR

**Total Inputs:** Combination of inputs from methods 3, 4, and 5  
**Frequency:** Daily (after interpolation)  
**Transformation:** Weighted combination of indices

### 10.1 Component Indices (3 inputs)

| # | Index | Source Method | Frequency | Inputs |
|---|-------|---------------|-----------|--------|
| 1 | $\text{SENT}_t^{BW-PLS}$ | Baker-Wurgler PLS | Monthly → Daily | 6 sentiment proxies + macro controls |
| 2 | $\text{RORO}_t^{IMF}$ | IMF SVAR | Daily | 21 VAR variables (spreads, factors, contagion) |
| 3 | $\text{RORO}_t^{KC}$ | Kansas City Fed PCA | Daily | 18 financial series |

### 10.2 Weighting Schemes

#### 10.2.1 Inverse Variance Weighting

**Inputs Required:**
- Forecast variance per index: $\hat{\sigma}_i^2$ estimated on validation set
- Target: Credit spread change $\Delta S_{t+h}$

**Weights:**
$$\omega_i = \frac{\sigma_i^{-2}}{\sum_j \sigma_j^{-2}}$$

#### 10.2.2 Predictive PLS Regression

**Inputs Required:**
- Matrix: $\mathbf{R}_t = [\text{SENT}_t^{BW}, \text{RORO}_t^{IMF}, \text{RORO}_t^{KC}]$
- Target: $\Delta S_{t+h}$

**Cross-Covariance:**
$$\mathbf{c} = \frac{1}{T}\sum_{t=1}^{T} \mathbf{R}_t \cdot \Delta S_{t+h}$$

**PLS Weight:**
$$\boldsymbol{\omega}^{PLS} = \frac{\mathbf{c}}{\|\mathbf{c}\|}$$

#### 10.2.3 Conformal-Optimized Weighting

**Inputs Required:**
- Grid of weights: $\boldsymbol{\omega} \in \{(w_1, w_2, w_3) : \sum w_i = 1, w_i \geq 0\}$
- Calibration set: $\{(X_i, Y_i)\}$ where $X_i = \boldsymbol{\omega}^\top \mathbf{R}_i$
- Coverage target: $1-\alpha$

**Optimization:**
$$\boldsymbol{\omega}^* = \arg\min_{\boldsymbol{\omega}} \left\{\bar{W}(\boldsymbol{\omega}) : \hat{\text{Cov}}(\boldsymbol{\omega}) \geq 1-\alpha\right\}$$

### 10.3 Combined Signal

**Output:**
$$\text{Signal}_t^{\text{Hybrid}} = \omega_1 \cdot \text{SENT}_t^{BW-PLS} + \omega_2 \cdot \text{RORO}_t^{IMF} + \omega_3 \cdot \text{RORO}_t^{KC}$$

